while 17 persons are on ventilator support.\n\nTill date, 12 districts have more than 500 active cases. The districts with over 500 active cases are Morang, Sunsari, Parsa, Bara, Rautahat, Sarlahi, Mahottari, Dhanusha, Chitwan, Lalitpur, Kathmandu and Rupandehi.\n\nMeanwhile, 11 more people lost their lives from coronavirus infection in the last 24 hours. With this, the death toll from the virus reached 239 in Nepal.","title":"Kathmandu Valley records 481 COVID-19 cases in highest single-day spike - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2020/01/124308/","video":[]}
